### Tested versions

Reproducible in (all tested with Forward+ renderer):
- v4.5.rc2.official [2dd26a027] (tested also Compatibility renderer, same result)
- v4.4.1.stable.official [49a5bc7b6]
- v4.3.stable.official [77dcf97d8]
- v4.2.2.stable.official [15073afe3]
- v4.1.4.stable.official [fe0e8e557]
- v4.0.4.stable.official [fc0b241c9]

### System information

Godot v4.4.1.stable - Windows 10 (build 19045) - Multi-window, 1 monitor - Vulkan (Forward+) - integrated AMD Radeon(TM) Graphics (Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.; 31.0.21923.11000) - AMD Ryzen 5 5600G with Radeon Graphics (12 threads)

### Issue description

Title. Example:
```gdshader
float a = 3.0;
float b = 3.0;
float result_variables = mod(a, b);
float result_literals = mod(3.0, 3.0);
```
For the above `result_literals` is correctly `0.0`, but `result_variables` is `3.0`.

<img width="1022" height="716" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0486a798-4e58-4d3c-a044-66b8bb710934" />|<img width="1022" height="716" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/70035975-ce81-4731-951a-c126e3042868" />
-|-

---

This bug can be observed e.g. when using particle animations. Example: for a 3x2 frame layout 4th frame UVs are broken (because of the mentioned incorrect `mod(3.0, 3.0)` result).

<img width="427" height="512" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cbe6f33a-b331-4874-974e-166e6eefebc1" />

<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1f893101-9d2c-4f81-9603-e7393dc84c9c" />|<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d17398e2-b2e8-42c8-83c2-33b2d0c541cc" />|<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a1702bd8-9d6c-463d-8d9b-415cbd106833" />
-|-|-
<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/98c0f59f-bcf2-4f6d-9247-23986fee1b88" />|<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/104512d8-cbf4-4204-b738-b2254fa4171f" />|<img width="479" height="522" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/11adc031-97e1-4504-b442-fed7a511bf14" />

Basically 4th frame ends up with this UV region:
<img width="311" height="199" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1084f356-14da-4cfd-9d9b-86cee29b226b" />

Thus enabling texture repeat works as a workaround.

<img width="674" height="580" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8c4aff7b-bd0f-4aac-99bd-827efb81ff91" />|<img width="674" height="580" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f8e1e52-a591-4370-8a21-94da7d5f806b" />
-|-

### Steps to reproduce

Apply such shader, toggle `bugged_mod` parameter:
```gdshader
shader_type canvas_item;

uniform bool bugged_mod = false;

void fragment() {
	float a = 3.0;
	float b = 3.0;
	float mod_result = bugged_mod ? mod(a, b) : mod(3.0, 3.0);

	if (mod_result == 3.0) {
		COLOR.r = 1.0;
	}
	if (mod_result == 0.0) {
		COLOR.g = 1.0;
	}
}
```

